Pam's House
Location: Lino Lakes, MN

Architectural Transition & Refinement: Circle Pines & Lino Lakes, MN

In this unique Circle Pines/Lino Lakes project for Pam Caron, we were tasked with unifying a transitional "breezeway" space that serves as a sunroom and reading nook. The primary challenge was the accent wall—a rugged, exterior-grade wood siding that remained from the original structure after the breezeway was enclosed. We performed a detailed repaint of the ceiling and door systems, transitioning the dark, heavy door trim into a crisp, modern finish that bridges the gap between the interior comfort and the rustic accent wall. By expertly coating the diverse substrates of the ceiling, smooth trim, and textured wood siding, we transformed a functional pass-through into a cohesive, high-end sanctuary. This project demonstrates how professional painting can harmonize "exterior" materials with "interior" luxury to create a perfectly balanced living space.